POLICE are following a line of inquiry after a man was attacked in Glasgow city centre. Police probe attack on man in city centre POLICE are following a line of inquiry after a man was attacked in Glasgow city centre.Officers were called to Midland Street, near Central Station, after the man was found with serious head injuries.A spokeswoman for Police Scotland said they were called out at around 5am after the man was discovered.He was taken to the Glasgow Royal Infirmary for treatment. 